Biography

Daniel Rodney Hennessy was born on 3 March 1904 in Janesville, Waseca, Minnesota, United States, son of John E Hennessy and Cora Louella Howard.

Daniel, son of John E. Hennesay & Cora S. H..., was born on 3 March 1904 in Janesville, Waseca, Minnesota, United States.[1]

In the 1910 census Daniel (age 6) was the son of John E Hennessy in Excelsior, Hennepin, Minnesota, United States.[2]

In the 1920 census D (age 15) was the single son of J E Hennesy in Excelsior, Hennepin, Minnesota, United States.[3]

In the 1930 census Neil (age 26) was the single son of J E Hennessy in Shorewood, Hennepin, Minnesota, United States.[4]

Neil's child Helen Kathleen Hennessy was born on 27 July 1935 in Hennepin, Minnesota, United States.[5]

In the 1940 census N (age 36) was the married head of household in Eugene Election Precinct 14, Lane, Oregon, United States.[6]

Neil was in a military record on 16 February 1942 in Eugene, Lane, Oregon, United States.[7]

N was mentioned in the obituary of his another person on 26 April 1949 in Olympia, Washington.[8]

Neil (age 58) married Edna L Roark (age 61) on 15 August 1962 in Nevada, California.[9]

Neil, son of Howard, died (age 78) on 24 April 1982 in Nevada, California, United States.[10][11]

Neil died on 24 April 1982 and was buried in Nevada City, Nevada, California, United States.[12]
